Package: geex
Type: Package
Title: A Framework for Estimating Equations
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Bradley Saul
Maintainer: Bradley Saul <bradleysaul@gmail.com>
Description: Provides a framework for estimating parameters from a set of estimating equations. Computes large sample variance using M-estimation theory as detailed by L.A. Stefanski and D.D. Boos in "The Calculus of M-estimation" (The American Statistician (2002), 56(1), 29-38). Also computes finite sample corrections proposed by M.P. Fay, and B.I. Graubard in "Small-Sample adjustments for wald-type tests using sandwich estimators" (Biometrics (2001), 57(4), 1198-1206).
Depends:
  R (>= 3.1)
Imports:
  Matrix (>= 1.2-6),
  rootSolve (>= 1.6.6),
  numDeriv (>= 2014.2-1)
Suggests:
  testthat,
  knitr
License: GPL (>= 2)
LazyData: TRUE
VignetteBuilder: knitr
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
